<ProsePage
  title="About HomeStem"
  description="HomeStem publishes tested, no-nonsense home & garden buying guides and how-tos."
  path="/about"
>
  <p>
    HomeStem is a home &amp; garden publication for people who'd rather get it
    right the first time. We test, research, and compare the gear that makes
    indoor plants, balconies, small spaces, and yards easier to live with — then
    tell you plainly what's worth buying.
  </p>

  <h2>What we cover</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Indoor Plants</strong> — care, grow lights, and the gear that keeps your plants thriving.</li>
    <li><strong>Small Space Org</strong> — storage and organization for apartments and compact homes.</li>
    <li><strong>Lawn &amp; Outdoor</strong> — tools and tips for a healthier yard.</li>
    <li><strong>Balcony Garden</strong> — planters and low-maintenance ideas for balconies and patios.</li>
    <li><strong>Home Decor</strong> — finishing touches that make a house feel like home.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>How we make money</h2>
  <p>
    HomeStem is reader-supported. We use affiliate links — primarily through the
    Amazon Associates program — and may earn a commission when you buy through
    them, at no extra cost to you. Commissions never influence our
    recommendations. Read our
    <a href="/affiliate-disclosure">Affiliate Disclosure</a> for the full story.
  </p>

  <h2>Our approach</h2>
  <p>
    Every recommendation is grounded in hands-on testing and research, written
    for a US audience, and checked for current relevance and pricing. If
    something isn't worth your money, we'll say so.
  </p>
</ProsePage>
